Task 2.1 – Multiple Choice (5 mins)
Question:
What does app.use(express.json()) do in Express?
a) Parses HTML forms
b) Parses JSON request bodies
c) Serves static files
d) Handles cookies

Ans--(b) Parses JSON request bodies

Task 2.2 – API Design

HTTP Method

DELETE

Route Structure
DELETE /api/users/:id

Sample Request
DELETE /api/users/64a123xyz

Sample Response (Success)
{
  "message": "User deleted successfully"
}

Sample Response (Not Found)
{
  "message": "User not found"
}

Task 2.3 – Coding (Express Server)

const express = require("express");
const app = express();

app.get("/status", (req, res) => {
  res.json({ message: "Server is running" });
});

app.listen(4000, () => {
  console.log("Server running on port 4000");
});
